dan200.computercraft.api.turtle

Interface ITurtleCommand


  • public interface ITurtleCommand
    An interface for objects executing custom turtle commands, used with ITurtleAccess.issueCommand
    See Also:
    ITurtleAccess.executeCommand(dan200.computercraft.api.lua.ILuaContext,ITurtleCommand)

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      TurtleCommandResult execute(ITurtleAccess turtle)
      Will be called by the turtle on the main thread when it is time to execute the custom command.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        TurtleCommandResult execute(ITurtleAccess turtle)
        Will be called by the turtle on the main thread when it is time to execute the custom command. The handler should either perform the work of the command, and return success, or return failure with an error message to indicate the command cannot be executed at this time.
        Parameters:
        turtle - access to the turtle for whom the command was issued
        Returns:
        TurtleCommandResult.success() or TurtleCommandResult.failure( errorMessage )
        See Also:
        ITurtleAccess.executeCommand(dan200.computercraft.api.lua.ILuaContext,ITurtleCommand), TurtleCommandResult
